<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="529" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1037,1063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished by the forewing having two discocellular stigmata, the irregularly circled juxta arched outward lateromedially, and produced postero- and anteromedially, and the aedeagus with a large sub-triangular sclerite from about distal 1/4 reaching near apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="529" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" box="[199,745,1145,1172]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1145,1171]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[429,498,1145,1171]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1394,1418]" captionTargetBox="[199,1384,186,1358]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[170,1417,178,1373]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Adults of Ripeacma spp. 9, R. stigmosa sp. nov.; 10, R. acerba sp. nov.; 11, R. ellipsoidea sp. nov.; 12, R. hamatispina sp. nov.; 13, R. mediprocessa sp. nov.; 14, R. trilobata sp. nov., paratype, ♀. All holotypes and males, except paratype and female for R. trilobata. Scales = 1.00 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911457/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[638,741,1145,1172]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="8" pageNumber="529" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1181,1207]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Head</emphasis>
whitish yellow. Labial palpus yellow, with black scales on outer surface. Antenna yellow; scape with black scales and flagellum ringed with black on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1253,1279]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Thorax</emphasis>
and tegula black basally, yellow distally. Forewing yellow, with yellowish brown scales; costal margin with a wide black band along basal 1/3, with a large semicircular black spot at middle and two–three black dots in distal 1/3; discal, discocellular and plical stigmata black, discocellular stigmata doubled, placed one above the other; terminal dots black, evenly spaced along termen to tornus; fringe grey along termen and dorsum. Hindwing and fringe grey. Legs yellow; coxa of foreleg black on ventral surface; on dorsal surface, femur and tibia of foreleg black, tibia of midleg black, with yellow streak at basal 1/3, at middle and at apex, tarsi of fore- and midlegs black at middle of first tarsomere and at base of second tarsomere as well as on entire third and fourth tarsomeres, femur of hindleg with black scales; on outer surface, tibia of hindleg with black scales at base and on distal half, tarsus black at middle of first tarsomere and at base of second tarsomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1577,1603]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[382,467,1577,1603]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1719,1743]" captionTargetBox="[173,1401,191,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[173,1413,181,1695]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Male genitalia of Ripeacma spp. 21, R. stigmosa sp. nov., slide No. LiSR16228; 22, R. acerba sp. nov., slide No. LiSR17013; 23, R. ellipsoidea sp. nov., slide No. LiSR16270; 24, R. hamatispina sp. nov., slide No. LiSR16284; 25, R. mediprocessa sp. nov., slide No. XZX20421; 26, R. trilobata sp. nov., slide No. XZX20424. All holotypes. Scales = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911463/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Uncus elongate triangular, narrowed from wide base to pointed apex, with a seta at middle laterally. Gnathos membranous, ventral plate indistinct. Tegumen uniformly wide medially, with a large Vshaped anterior emargination; lateral arms slightly narrowed to apex, longer than median width. Valva with costal and ventral margins subparallel, apex obtusely rounded, with a tuft of stout long setae at basal 1/3 above ventral margin; costa uniformly banded, reaching tip of costal margin; transtilla lobes uniformly banded, joined mesially by membrane; sacculus triangular, more sclerotized apically. Saccus wide at base, narrowed to basal 1/3, distal 2/3 clubbed, with a small elliptical membranous lobe apically. Juxta a large irregular circle, arched outward laterally, produced postero- and anteromedially. Aedeagus about 3/4 length of valva, tapered to pointed apex; banded process extending from before laterobasal 1/3 to middle length of aedeagus, then fused and produced to a triangular process distally; large sub-triangular sclerite from about distal 1/4 reaching near apex, with a tooth at each angle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,893,2036]" box="[199,401,1937,1963]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
